{
  "texts": [
    "From our human subject study, we have learned that intentional and structured guidance during hypothesis generation can facilitate the process, at least among inexperienced clinical researchers.",
    "VIADS, as an example of a potential tool, appears to make the hypothesis generation process more efficient, that is, significantly faster, by using significantly fewer cognitive events.",
    "Meanwhile, the number of hypotheses generated was similar between the VIADS and control groups.",
    "Regarding the quality of the hypotheses, the control group was slightly higher in validity, significance, and the feasibility is statistically significantly higher.",
    "We do notice the hypotheses generated by the VIADS groups seemed more complicated than those generate by the control groups."
  ]
}